# GameBoard Pro — environment variables
# The MVP runs fully on seeded mock data with NO env vars required.
# These are the wires for going to production later.

# --- Neon (Free Postgres) — used by Drizzle ---
# Create a project at https://neon.tech and paste the pooled connection string.
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@host/dbname?sslmode=require"

# --- Clerk (Free Auth) — manager login ---
# Create an app at https://clerk.com. With these keys, editing & configuration
# routes require a signed-in manager while the staff/print views stay public.
# Without them the app falls back to the local Manager/Staff toggle so the MVP
# stays fully usable with zero setup.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=""
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=""
# Optional: keep modal sign-in (defaults are fine for most setups)
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL="/"
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL="/"

# --- Live schedule feed ---
# The Full Schedule + live board pull from ESPN's free public API server-side.
# No key required. (In a sandbox with a network egress allowlist, the host
# site.api.espn.com must be allowed; on Netlify it works out of the box.)

# --- Resend (Free email) — morning board email ---
# Create a key at https://resend.com. Without it, "Send board" is a safe no-op.
RESEND_API_KEY=""
# Verified sender. Free tier can use onboarding@resend.dev (to your own address);
# verify a domain for real sending, e.g. "Hooligans GameBoard <board@yourbar.com>".
RESEND_FROM="GameBoard Pro <onboarding@resend.dev>"
# Automated morning send (Netlify scheduled function netlify/functions/morning-board):
EMAIL_CRON_TOKEN=""            # any long random string; protects the cron endpoint
MORNING_BOARD_TO=""           # comma-separated recipient emails for the auto morning email
